description:
Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following four stories:

  • I Walked Through the Doors of Destiny!
  • I Made a Pact With "Them"!
  • Land Ho!
  • We Fought the Giant of Island X!

The issue also features the following small comic strips:

  • Professor Eureka
  • Moolah the Mystic

I Walked Through the Doors of Destiny

Emmet Kane and John Carson are looking for the best new carnival attraction when they find Omar the Mystic's House of 100 Doors! Behind each door contains a scene that'll evoke a new emotion, but what'll happen when Emmet Kane becomes hypnotized by the effects that the doors have on him?

I Made a Pact With 'Them'

Adam Perry always believed that if he had the skills and abilities of others that he'd be able to put them to much better use. Adam's wishes come true after he becomes a scientific experiment for a group of Atlantians, but these powers come with a price!

Land Ho!

Survivors of a ship wreck try to cope with their current situation.

We Fought the Giant of Island X

The atomic island of Island X has been revisited by a group of scientists. Unfortunately, their experiment goes haywire and one of the scientists turns into a giant. Desperate for help he calls for one of his friends to come help, but things get complicated once the army learns of his existence

Professor Eureka

Professor Eureka is looking for a hidden city.

Moolah the Mystic

Moolah meets someone else who can tell fortunes!
name: We Fought the Giant of Island X!

description:
Batmantown, U.S.A.

The mayor of Plainville decides to rename the town after Batman to attract more tourists and increase the general population. Batmantown is apparently crime free but when the Dynamic Duo learn a known gangster is resident there, they decide to investigate. On arriving in Batmantown, Bruce Wayne and Dick Grayson pretend to be actors and audition to play Batman and Robin in a pageant in their honour. Using this opportunity, the heroes uncover a plot to rob the entire town.

The Hunters of Gotham City

A ship transporting exotic animals from around the world to Gotham City Zoo crashes at the pier and a number of animals manage to escape. Batman and Robin help the Zoologist and his assistant to round up the escaped animals one by one and discover that some of the animals may have been used for smuggling diamonds.

The Great Batman Contest

Batman and Robin decide to add to their arsenal of gadgets and offer a fully paid scholarship in Criminology to the contest winner who can invent a new Bat-gadget. After receiving enough entrants to fill up the Batcave, the Dynamic Duo narrow it down to the last four. Each gadget is then used in an actual mission to help solve crime and wait till you see the winner!
name: [100th Batman Issue!]
